casebody.data:
Dayton Bar Association v. Hanaghan.

[Cite as Dayton Bar Assn. v. Hanaghan (1992), 64 Ohio St.3d 457.]

(No. 92-834 Submitted June 2, 1992 Decided September 2, 1992.) *458Bieser, Greer & Landis and Howard P. Krisher, for relator. *459Charles W. Kettlewell, for respondent. Per Curiam.

We agree with the board’s findings and recommendation. Respondent is hereby publicly reprimanded. Costs taxed to respondent.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
